TYPE ERROR: Effect laundering in impl of 'speak' for interface 'Speak': the body performs <Stdout>, which is not sourced from any argument and is not declared by the method's effect row, so a caller can instantiate the method's effect variable to <> and a function typed pure would then silently perform it. Either declare the effect as a concrete label in the method's return row (e.g. `<Stdout>`), or perform it only through an argument (a callback carrying `<e>`) so the caller sees it.
